## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-payments
instruction: Click "Payments & Denials" in the main sidebar, then click the "Deposits" tab.
success_criteria: The Deposits tab is active. You can see a list of deposits grouped by month, most recent expanded.
anchor: "Deposits"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Payments & Denials" link is in the sidebar. Once there, click the "Deposits" tab.

### step 2
id: read-summary-strip
instruction: Read the summary strip at the top: total amount received, count of auto-posted deposits, and count of deposits needing review.
success_criteria: You can see the key payment totals at a glance.
anchor: "summary strip"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The summary strip is displayed at the very top of the deposits table.

### step 3
id: filter-if-needed
instruction: Optionally filter by payer name or posting status (All, Auto-Posted, Needs Review, Posted, Exception) using the controls above the table.
success_criteria: Filters applied (or skipped). The deposit list shows what you want to see.
anchor: "payer filter"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Filter controls are above the deposits table.

### step 4
id: review-deposit-rows
instruction: Read the deposits table. Each row shows date, check/EFT number, payer name, amount, posting status, and reconciliation status. Click any row to open that deposit and see individual claim payments.
success_criteria: You understand incoming payment activity and have opened a specific deposit if needed.
anchor: "deposits table"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click on any row to see the breakdown of individual claim payments within that deposit.

## Completion Message
you can see all incoming payments here. any deposits with "Needs Review" or "Exception" status need attention — click into them to resolve posting issues. the Remittances tab breaks down individual claim-level payments.

